.Dd May 9, 2026
.Dt DSEARCH 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm dsearch
.Nd recursively search a directory for files by name
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm dsearch
.Ar folder
.Ar name
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
walks
.Ar folder
and all of its subdirectories, printing the full path of every file
or directory whose name contains
.Ar name
as a substring.
The search is case-sensitive.
.Pp
Symbolic links are not followed.
Permission errors on individual directories are reported to standard
error but do not stop the search.
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It 0
At least one match was found.
.It 1
No matches were found, or an error occurred (wrong usage, starting
path does not exist, etc.).
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
Search
.Pa /home/user/documents
for any file or directory whose name contains
.Dq report :
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ dsearch /home/user/documents report
.Ed
.Sh DIAGNOSTICS
Warnings about unreadable directories are printed to standard error
and the exit status reflects whether any match was found.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr find 1 ,
.Xr ls 1
.Sh AUTHORS
Written as a minimal, portable POSIX tool.
